policy_summary: 500 megawatts of power is to be generated from renewable sources by 2020. There will be a 13.6% reduction in GHG emissions by 2030 compared to a business.

policy_description: Andorra’s NDC does not set a stronger commitment by 2030 but proposes a net-zero emissions by 2050. The goal is to reach 193,73 GgCO2e. The implementation period is set to be between 2021 and 2030 and covers all GHG and F-gases. | Andorra’s NDC does not set a stronger commitment by 2030 but proposes a net-zero emissions by 2050. The goal is to reach 193,73 GgCO2e. The implementation period is set to be between 2021 and 2030 and covers all GHG and F-gases.
policy_summary: Andorra’s NDC does not set a stronger commitment by 2030 but proposes a net-zero emissions by 2050. The goal is to reach 193,73 GgCO2e. The implementation period is set to be between 2021 and 2030.

policy_description: The NDC of Antigua and Barbuda focuses on adaptation measures, improved energy efficiency standards, and support for renewable energy deployment. Targets include: Conditional Adaptation Targets by 2025, increase seawater desalination capacity by 50% above 2015 levels. Conditional Mitigation Targets By 2020, establish efficiency standards for the importation of all vehicles and appliances. | The NDC of Antigua and Barbuda focuses on adaptation measures, improved energy efficiency standards, and support for renewable energy deployment. Targets include: Conditional Adaptation Targets by 2025, increase seawater desalination capacity by 50% above 2015 levels. Conditional Mitigation Targets By 2020, establish efficiency standards for the importation of all vehicles and appliances.
policy_summary: The NDC of Antigua and Barbuda focuses on adaptation measures, improved energy efficiency standards, and support for renewable energy deployment. Targets include: Conditional Adaptation Targets by 2025, increase seawater desalination capacity by 50% above 2015 levels. Conditional Mitigation Targets By 2020, establish efficiency standards for the importation of all vehicles and appliances.

policy_description: The national emission target for Austria under the EU Effort Sharing Decision is 16% reduction of greenhouse gas emissions in 2020. policy_description: Brunei submitted its NDC using 2015 as reference year (emissions of 11.6MtCO2e) and committing itself to a reduction in greenhouse gas (GHG) emissions by 20% relative to Business-As-Usual levels in 2030. The Government also further aspires to generate at least 10% of total power from new and renewable resources by 2035. policy_description: Bhutan is a net sink for greenhouse gases. The estimated sequestration capacity of our forest is 6.3 million tons of CO2. policy_description: Canada's Greenhouse Gas (GHG) Offset Credit System enables project proponents to generate federal offset credits if they register and implement projects that reduce GHGs. General Canada is developing a federal GHG offset system that would cover activities not covered by carbon pricing. Canada aims to create a net-zero electricity grid by 2035. policy_summary: Canada's Greenhouse Gas (GHG) Offset Credit System enables project proponents to generate federal offset credits if they register and implement projects that reduce GHGs. Canada aims to create a net-zero electricity grid by 2035.

policy_description: Switzerland has a legal & legally binding GHG reduction target. The Federal Energy Law was adopted by the Parliament in September 2016 and entered into force on 1 January 2018. policy_description: The Spanish government released an Energy Efficiency Action Plan for 2008 to 2012 to assist with implementation of the Spanish Energy Efficiency Strategy (E4) 2004-2012. The E4 plan aims to cut Spanish energy use by 8.5% by 2008, thus reducing total carbon dioxide emissions by 32.5 Mt. policy_description: Residents of Tallinn can use public transportation for free. A green card, delivered to locals for 2€, only applies to residents. policy_description: Fiji is committed to reach net-zero emissions by 2050. Fiji’s NDC uses as reference year 2013 to project a BAU scenario estimating 2,341 kTCO2 by the energy sector by 2030. Fiji established a sectoral target of reducing 30% of energy sector emissions. | Fiji is committed to reach net-zero emissions by 2050. Fiji’s NDC uses as reference year 2013 to project a BAU scenario estimating 2,341 kTCO2 by the energy sector by 2030. Fiji established a sectoral target of reducing 30% of energy sector emissions. | Fiji is committed to reach net-zero emissions by 2050. Fiji’s NDC uses as reference year 2013 to project a BAU scenario estimating 2,341 kTCO2 by the energy sector by 2030. policy_summary: Fiji established a sectoral target of reducing 30% of energy sector emissions. Fiji is committed to reach net-zero emissions by 2050. Fiji’s NDC uses as reference year 2013 to project a BAU scenario estimating 2,341 kTCO2.

policy_description: Government of India launched the National Electric Mobility Mission Plan (NEMMP) 2020 in 2013. There is an ambitious target to achieve 6-7 million sales of hybrid and electric vehicles year on year from 2020 onwards. India has a target of 500 GW of RE capacity by 2030, increasing the previous target by 50 GW in 2030. Government buildings have to be equipped with at least three-star labelled products (residential and non-residential) Renewable energy target of 175 GW to be achieved by 2022. | Government of India launched the National Electric Mobility Mission Plan (NEMMP) 2020 in 2013. policy_description: Monaco has set the goal to reduce its greenhouse gas emissions by 55% by 2030 and to reach net-zero by 2050. Monaco’s NDC covers all sectors and gases. For CO2, CH4 and N2O the reference year is 1990 and for F-gases thereference year is 1995. There is no agriculture sector in the country. | Monaco has set the goal to reduce its greenhouse gas emissions by 55% by 2030 and to reach net-zero by 2050. policy_description: The State of Palestine's updated NDC submission presents two targets under a Status quo scenario, and an independence scenario. These targets are set for 2040, and set out a 17.5% and 26.6% reduction in GHG emissions compared to a BAU scenario respectively.
policy_summary: The State of Palestine's updated NDC submission presents two targets under a Status quo scenario, and an independence scenario. These targets are set for 2040, and set out a 17.5% and 26.6% reduction in GHG emissions compared to a BAU scenario respectively.

policy_summary: French Overseas Countries and Territories commit an economy-wide plan of limiting the increase in GHG emissions to 8.4% in 2030 compared to 2016.
